** 
# select objects with the left mouse button 

## when you left-click on the table and drag
- The selection square is stretched.
- all objects included in the selection are included
- when pressed shift with the left  button on the object it is added to the selection 

## selected objects 
- pulled together.
- will be added to the hand together if puled in heand.
- right button menu have command - copy objects .

# "coping list" description of the term
## "coping list" 
- This is an analogue of the internal clipboard for copying and pasting objects.
- list of copied items not visually displayed anywhere.  
- all objects have right button menu command - copy object. 
- on command - copy object. object is copied in the "coping list".

## table have right button menu command.
- When user right-click in an empty area of the table openenig right button menu command.
- it have "past" command
- on "past" command - on the cursor position is inserted all object from "coping list", on the table where the cursor position is.

## When user press control+v,
- on the cursor position is inserted all object from "coping list", on the table where the cursor position is.
- if the cursor position is on the hand panel, then it is inserted into the hand.

# copy objects and delete 
## dragged object that is, the object that is currently being dragged
when pressed:
- control+с
  The dragged object is copied in the "coping list" 
- control+x 
  The dragged object is deleted and copied to the "coping list".

